**Segments**

The herbal tea market can be segmented based on type, packaging, distribution channel, and geography. In terms of type, the market can be categorized into green tea, black tea, oolong tea, white tea, and others. Green tea is anticipated to have significant growth due to its various health benefits and antioxidant properties. Packaging segments include loose tea, tea bags, and ready-to-drink herbal teas. Tea bags are expected to dominate this segment due to their convenience and ease of use. Distribution channels for herbal tea consist of supermarkets/hypermarkets, specialty stores, online retail, and others. With the increasing trend of online shopping, the online retail segment is projected to witness substantial growth. Geographically, the market can be divided into North America, Europe, Asia-Pacific, South America, and the Middle East & Africa. Asia-Pacific is expected to hold a considerable share in the herbal tea market due to the rich tea culture in countries like China and India.

